[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    130[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Issue 5 - NOTE: `compute_holdout_calibration` WIS approximation is simplified but the comment does not flag the simplification
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Severity:** NOTE
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **File:** `chapter12.09-python-example.md`, `compute_holdout_calibration`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Approximate WIS contribution: penalty for distance
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # outside the 95 interval plus interval width.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m width = q975 - q025
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m if actual < q025:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     wis_total += width + 2 * (q025 - actual) / 0.05
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m elif actual > q975:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     wis_total += width + 2 * (actual - q975) / 0.05
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     wis_total += width
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The real Weighted Interval Score (Bracher et al. 2021) sums over multiple quantile pairs (not just the 95% interval) with specific alpha-level weights. The demo's approximation uses only the 95% interval, which produces a score that correlates with the real WIS but has different magnitude and sensitivity properties. This is fine for a teaching example but a reader who uses this as their calibration metric will get different rankings than the standard WIS.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Fix:** Add a brief comment:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Simplified WIS using only the 95% interval. The full WIS
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # (Bracher et al. 2021) sums over all quantile pairs in the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # grid with alpha-specific weights. Production uses the full
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # formulation for proper model ranking.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
