[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Seven module-level boto3 handles are constructed (`s3_client`, `dynamodb`, `kinesis_client`, `eventbridge_client`, `cloudwatch_client`, `sagemaker_runtime`, `lambda_client`). The demo wires up mocks and never references the real handles. boto3 client creation is lazy (no network call until use), so this causes no runtime issue, but a learner may wonder why they exist.
